history.text: What do you think of the voice cast of Frozen?
They were good.
Do you think the rating given to the movie was fair? Which was most fair?
I think the ratings are fair. I think the Rotten Tomatoes rating is closest to how I would rate the movie
I agree! It seems fair considering how much people seemed to like the movie. Who was your favorite character?
The snowman, but I can't remember his name.
I think it was an interesting choice to have multiple voice actors for the same characters at different ages. What are your thoughts on that?
It was probably challenging for the actors unless they manipulated their voices electronically. Am I supposed to ask you questions too or just respond to yours?

Yes it was definitely essential if they wanted a younger cast throughout the movie. And I think having the characters at multiple ages was essential to what they wanted to do seeing as it was well-liked. You can ask questions as well, I believe. This is supposed to be an engaging conversation about the movie.
Did you know it was in 3D? For some reason I didn't know that.
Yes! I think that might have made the scene where Elsa accidentally hurts Anna more powerful. Do you think that Elsa has cool powers?
Her powers were cool. I didn't know they were making it into a play did you?
I think they are saying it could be made into a play, not that they would. But it would be a nice play!
Have you read the book it was based on?
I have not! I haven't read most of Hans Christian Andesen's work, but this one I hadn't even heard of. Have you?
No, I haven't read much of Andersen's works. What was your favorite song?
I am not sure what songs there were, but what did you think of the Duke of Weselton?
The Duke wasn't very nice! Who was it that proposed to Anna?
Hans ended up proposing to Anna, but Elsa was not a fan. Do you think she overreacted?
Maybe a bit! Do you think it was wise of Elsa to suppress her magic rather than mastering it?
I definitely think it wasn't a good idea. Perhaps it was the fact that her parents died when she was a teenager and they didn't give her much direction. THey probably could have helped her practice.
Do you think it was a good idea to separate the girls after Elsa injured Anna?
I don't think so. They have such tumult later in life, with Elsa accidentally freezing Anna's heart. Then Hans is so cruel to the both of them.
Did you expect Hans would be so cruel?
What did you think of Marshmallow? I sort of suspected that Hans wasn't what he seemed, he was just too perfect.

Marshmallow seems to be an embodiment of the "evil" of Elsa. He is the cruel ice monster that hurts Anna, Kristoff, and Olaf in their journey. However, it is a super cute name. Unfortunately he is mean.
Elsa is only 21. Do you think that is young to become a queen?
Maybe a little young, but I'm sure others might have been younger. What was it that could reverse the spell placed on Anna?
They said it was an act of true love, but Hans ended up not allowing that to happen. He could never have been the act of true love that was needed.
It seems the trolls know the most about Elsa's magic. They should have trained her from the start!
I hope this ends soon, I having trouble coming up with new questions! Was Elsa able to escape Hans?
She was able to escape her detention cell! Hopefully she could do more to stop him.
I agree that the trolls should have trained Elsa.
